Goal: Make it easy to evaluate and present.

1. Documentation
1. ER diagram and schema explanation
1. API docs with sample payloads
1. Setup and run instructions
1. Known limitations and assumptions

2. Demo script
1. Create users and group
1. Add expenses (equal + unequal)
1. Show balances
1. Record settlement
1. Show updated balances

3. Final package
1. SQL scripts
1. Backend and frontend source
1. Test evidence
1. Presentation slides

Deliverables:
1. Submission-ready project with reproducible demo

---

## **Parallel Work Strategy (Important)**
To avoid blocking and conflicts:

1. Run Phase 1 and Phase 2 in parallel after schema draft is frozen
1. Run Phase 3 once auth/group endpoints are stable
1. Run Phase 4 and Phase 5 in parallel using fixed API contracts
1. Start Phase 6 checks as soon as first expense flow exists
1. Keep Phase 7 continuous, not only at the end

---

## **MVP Acceptance Checklist**
1. User can signup/login
1. User can create/join group and view group list
1. Group member can add expense with equal/unequal split
1. Expense and split persist correctly in MySQL
1. App shows accurate who-owes-whom balances
1. Settlement updates balances correctly
1. Invalid operations are rejected safely
1. No partial writes on failed expense/settlement operations

